Apple has just given me one more reason to possibly switch to an iPhone&hellip;
iPhone opens to Exchange e-mail
I&rsquo;m currently using a Samsung BlackJack II, a Windows Mobile 6-based device with 3G connectivity. The e-mail functionality is great, but not having an easy way to keep my Address Book contacts in sync with my phone is a major hassle. It looks like using an iPhone would help address that.

You&rsquo;ve probably all run into the &ldquo;Unable to relay&rdquo; error message before. The usual fixes to this problem are pretty straightforward:
  Add the address space to a recipient policy in Exchange System Manager; this tell Exchange to accept the messages as inbound; or
  Add IP addresses, subnets, or host names to the SMTP virtual server in Exchange System Manager as allowed to relay through this host;
